1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:01:00,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.xyz Support Admin)

2
00:01:34,979 --> 00:01:37,780
[Bloom Life]

3
00:01:38,780 --> 00:01:43,610
[2007]

4
00:01:43,710 --> 00:01:45,440
I see a pilaf vendor over there.

5
00:01:45,930 --> 00:01:47,259
Pilaf. I love pilaf!

6
00:01:47,570 --> 00:01:48,450
Let's go.

7
00:01:49,289 --> 00:01:50,030
Dad,

8
00:01:50,180 --> 00:01:52,509
why are there
so many people in the bazaar?

9
00:01:52,789 --> 00:01:54,490
Because in our Kashgar,

10
00:01:54,770 --> 00:01:55,940
the bazaar is like a father,

11
00:01:55,940 --> 00:01:57,060
and also a mother.

12
00:01:57,690 --> 00:01:59,830
Anything can happen in the bazaar.

13
00:02:09,370 --> 00:02:09,970
Thank you.

14
00:02:10,979 --> 00:02:11,990
Lamb leg pilaf.

15
00:02:13,910 --> 00:02:14,660
Let me see.

16
00:02:20,620 --> 00:02:22,460
Look, what's this?

17
00:02:22,460 --> 00:02:23,660
A sheep knucklebone.

18
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:25,310
Then break it open for me to see.

19
00:02:25,310 --> 00:02:26,030
Okay.

20
00:02:26,910 --> 00:02:27,570
Here you go.

21
00:02:29,590 --> 00:02:30,620
One for each of us.

22
00:02:30,620 --> 00:02:32,020
Right, one for each of us.

23
00:02:41,920 --> 00:02:45,720
[Episode 2: Those Who Left
and Those Who Stayed]

24
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:58,780
One, two, three, four.

25
00:02:58,780 --> 00:03:01,910
Five, six, seven, eight.

26
00:03:02,630 --> 00:03:05,520
Two, two, three, four.

27
00:03:05,850 --> 00:03:09,280
Five, six, seven, eight.

28
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:13,020
Three, two, three, four.

29
00:03:13,020 --> 00:03:16,070
Five, six, seven, eight.

30
00:03:16,940 --> 00:03:17,410
Stop.

31
00:03:17,410 --> 00:03:18,590
Alright, let's take a break.

32
00:03:18,590 --> 00:03:21,590
Your feet are bleeding.
Can you still wear high heels?

33
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,470
Let me tell you,

34
00:03:24,570 --> 00:03:25,780
they suddenly announced today

35
00:03:25,780 --> 00:03:26,470
the casting for the lead actress

36
00:03:26,470 --> 00:03:27,470
of Alip and Sänäm.

37
00:03:27,620 --> 00:03:28,870
Sänäm is the role

38
00:03:28,870 --> 00:03:30,690
I've wanted to play since I was a child.

39
00:03:30,690 --> 00:03:31,850
If I wear flat shoes,

40
00:03:31,850 --> 00:03:33,970
how can I outshine those new girls?

41
00:03:34,290 --> 00:03:36,150
You‘re just looking for trouble.

42
00:03:38,390 --> 00:03:41,520
Why are you dressed
in the same color as the ancient city?

43
00:03:42,190 --> 00:03:43,650
These are Morandi colors.

44
00:03:43,650 --> 00:03:44,570
They are very classy.

45
00:03:44,570 --> 00:03:46,010
Looks like a sandstorm.

46
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:49,440
How is it?

47
00:03:50,060 --> 00:03:51,610
Compared to those fresh graduates,

48
00:03:51,610 --> 00:03:53,270
I can still hold my own, right?

49
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:55,340
You're the star of your troupe.

50
00:03:55,340 --> 00:03:57,730
Why are you comparing yourself
to a bunch of little girls?

51
00:03:57,730 --> 00:03:58,990
You don't understand.

52
00:03:59,060 --> 00:03:59,850
Alright,

53
00:03:59,850 --> 00:04:02,090
you couldn't be any prettier.

54
00:04:03,340 --> 00:04:04,190
Girls!

55
00:04:04,210 --> 00:04:05,410
For our troupe's revival of

56
00:04:05,410 --> 00:04:06,600
"Alip and Sänäm",

57
00:04:06,620 --> 00:04:07,840
besides showing

58
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:09,740
Sänäm's brave side,

59
00:04:09,740 --> 00:04:11,300
we must also give it a contemporary feel.

60
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:13,830
We need to focus on
portraying her as a woman

61
00:04:13,850 --> 00:04:15,320
with a spirit of self-pursuit.

62
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:16,620
Technically speaking,

63
00:04:16,620 --> 00:04:17,370
we

64
00:04:17,370 --> 00:04:18,899
will focus on using spins

65
00:04:18,899 --> 00:04:21,100
to express her rebellion against fate.

66
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,360
Good. Keep it up.

67
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:26,430
Come on, girls.

68
00:04:26,460 --> 00:04:27,550
Look alive.

69
00:04:29,190 --> 00:04:30,310
Good.

70
00:04:31,770 --> 00:04:32,540
Keep it up.

71
00:04:44,540 --> 00:04:45,330
Dad.

72
00:04:47,570 --> 00:04:48,390
Dad.

73
00:04:52,010 --> 00:04:52,810
Dad.

74
00:04:53,890 --> 00:04:56,370
Can we not let Mulading
fill out the forms anymore?

75
00:04:56,370 --> 00:04:58,940
His handwriting is so crooked,
even a sheep could write better.

76
00:04:58,940 --> 00:04:59,659
Others can't read it,

77
00:04:59,659 --> 00:05:01,590
and they send it back for me to redo.

78
00:05:02,630 --> 00:05:05,950
Is it wrong for him
to help you fill out the forms?

79
00:05:07,620 --> 00:05:08,890
Without him in the house,

80
00:05:08,890 --> 00:05:10,300
I would've died of exhaustion long ago.

81
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:12,070
Then you can teach me to make earthenware.

82
00:05:12,070 --> 00:05:13,180
I promise I'll do it better

83
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:14,310
and faster than him.

84
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:15,370
How can a woman

85
00:05:15,370 --> 00:05:16,430
make earthenware?

86
00:05:16,770 --> 00:05:18,570
Women can wash clothes and cook.

87
00:05:18,590 --> 00:05:20,450
Why can't they make earthenware?

88
00:05:20,540 --> 00:05:21,210
No way.

89
00:05:27,450 --> 00:05:28,860
Laili, you're back.

90
00:05:28,980 --> 00:05:30,450
I bought some figs.

91
00:05:30,450 --> 00:05:31,330
Try some.

92
00:05:34,130 --> 00:05:34,870
Mom!

93
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:37,020
Mom,

94
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:39,210
why did you let him wash my clothes?

95
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:41,500
I didn't look carefully.

96
00:05:41,540 --> 00:05:44,120
I hid them under my pillow on purpose.

97
00:05:44,620 --> 00:05:46,890
I said I'd wash them myself.

98
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:49,210
An apprentice is like a son.

99
00:05:49,490 --> 00:05:50,920
He is filial to his master.

100
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:52,240
So we should treat him

101
00:05:52,300 --> 00:05:53,330
like family.

102
00:05:53,350 --> 00:05:54,500
Even so,

103
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:55,420
family doesn't mean-

104
00:05:55,420 --> 00:05:56,350
What's the fuss?

105
00:05:56,430 --> 00:05:58,290
You'll marry him sooner or later.

106
00:05:58,330 --> 00:05:59,750
When did I say I'd marry him?

107
00:05:59,750 --> 00:06:00,550
Stop the fuss.

108
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:45,360
Great job, Minawar.

109
00:06:47,220 --> 00:06:47,830
Good.

110
00:06:47,860 --> 00:06:49,860
You didn't embarrass the veterans.

111
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:51,130
Back then, you relied on

112
00:06:51,130 --> 00:06:52,740
this eight-beat spinning trick

113
00:06:52,740 --> 00:06:53,800
to join our troupe.

114
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:55,620
You still have the skills.

115
00:06:55,620 --> 00:06:56,350
Good job.

116
00:06:58,980 --> 00:07:00,360
Minawar danced so well.

117
00:07:00,380 --> 00:07:02,230
Yes, she's amazing.

118
00:07:02,270 --> 00:07:03,420
It has to be Minawar.

119
00:07:03,420 --> 00:07:05,540
She's so stable even in high heels.

120
00:07:06,450 --> 00:07:08,300
She's truly our star.

121
00:07:08,940 --> 00:07:10,940
I was just doing what I had to.

122
00:07:12,130 --> 00:07:14,280
Band-Aids and plasters are in the drawer.

123
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:15,210
Take it easy.

124
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:41,630
Okay.

125
00:07:41,630 --> 00:07:44,060
I'll pack and send the pots later.

126
00:07:49,210 --> 00:07:50,100
Sorry.

127
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:51,830
What's going on here?

128
00:07:51,830 --> 00:07:53,620
He hit you. It's him.

129
00:07:55,330 --> 00:07:55,830
Sorry.

130
00:07:55,830 --> 00:07:56,870
I-I didn't mean to.

131
00:07:56,870 --> 00:07:58,440
I was playing football with them.

132
00:07:58,440 --> 00:07:59,690
Anyway, the ball didn't hit me.

133
00:07:59,690 --> 00:08:00,710
You hit me.

134
00:08:03,390 --> 00:08:04,850
What should I do?

135
00:08:04,950 --> 00:08:05,540
You tell me.

136
00:08:05,540 --> 00:08:06,690
Pay for it then.

137
00:08:06,940 --> 00:08:07,590
How much?

138
00:08:08,940 --> 00:08:09,690
600.

139
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:14,330
Okay.

140
00:08:14,540 --> 00:08:15,370
600 it is.

141
00:08:20,660 --> 00:08:21,100
Sorry.

142
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:22,060
I didn't bring any money

143
00:08:22,060 --> 00:08:22,690
or my phone today.

144
00:08:22,690 --> 00:08:23,000
I...

145
00:08:23,890 --> 00:08:26,290
You didn't bring money.
Are you kidding me?

146
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:28,060
Wait a minute.

147
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:32,360
I'll leave this bag with you as a deposit.

148
00:08:32,570 --> 00:08:33,450
What's this?

149
00:08:33,450 --> 00:08:35,850
These are my tools for making instruments.

150
00:08:40,179 --> 00:08:41,900
Then where can I find you?

151
00:08:41,900 --> 00:08:43,450
Adijiang Instrument Shop.

152
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:45,440
Adijiang Instrument Shop.

153
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:46,470
I live there.

154
00:09:04,990 --> 00:09:06,570
Come, sit inside.

155
00:09:06,570 --> 00:09:07,900
Come, please sit inside.

156
00:09:07,900 --> 00:09:08,490
No, thanks.

157
00:09:08,490 --> 00:09:10,280
Come inside.

158
00:09:20,190 --> 00:09:20,970
Dear guests,

159
00:09:22,450 --> 00:09:24,690
you've been sitting here for a while

160
00:09:24,710 --> 00:09:26,490
without ordering anything.

161
00:09:26,630 --> 00:09:28,440
Are you waiting for someone?

162
00:09:28,660 --> 00:09:30,190
Or is there something else?

163
00:09:30,260 --> 00:09:32,660
Go ask Adili about this.

164
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:35,130
So you're Adili's friends.

165
00:09:37,230 --> 00:09:38,370
Adili?

166
00:09:38,390 --> 00:09:40,320
He went out driving.

167
00:09:40,380 --> 00:09:41,920
He hasn't come back yet.

168
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:44,300
What do you want with Adili?

169
00:09:44,980 --> 00:09:47,910
Adili borrowed
some money from our company.

170
00:09:50,570 --> 00:09:52,450
Today is the day the money is due.

171
00:09:52,450 --> 00:09:53,160
Look.

172
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:00,520
We know about the contract,

173
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,050
but he hasn't come back.

174
00:10:02,050 --> 00:10:03,800
And we can't contact him either.

175
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:04,520
How about you...

176
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:05,980
There's no other options.

177
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:08,260
The contract is very clear.

178
00:10:08,260 --> 00:10:10,200
Today, either you give me the money,

179
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:12,290
or this shop belongs to me.

180
00:10:14,140 --> 00:10:16,330
Will they give us the money today?

181
00:10:18,810 --> 00:10:21,900
Today, either we get the money
or we get the shop.

182
00:10:30,870 --> 00:10:33,490
I'll mortgage these to you first.

183
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:36,990
My son will definitely
pay you back when he returns.

184
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:39,440
Just these?

185
00:10:57,040 --> 00:10:57,920
Let's go.

186
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:15,210
Good afternoon.

187
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:16,480
Good afternoon.

188
00:11:16,740 --> 00:11:18,010
You're in such a hurry to leave?

189
00:11:18,010 --> 00:11:18,750
Yeah.

190
00:11:18,780 --> 00:11:19,940
-Work won't wait for me.
-Let me.

191
00:11:19,940 --> 00:11:20,540
I'll do it.

192
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:23,740
-Give it to me.
-Didn't you get fired?

193
00:11:24,990 --> 00:11:26,560
That's not certain yet.

194
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:28,110
I can still try.

195
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:30,010
Why do people try so hard

196
00:11:30,030 --> 00:11:32,070
to become a piece of a jigsaw puzzle?

197
00:11:32,610 --> 00:11:33,730
What do you mean?

198
00:11:34,040 --> 00:11:34,800
If I were you,

199
00:11:34,830 --> 00:11:35,800
I wouldn't go to work.

200
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:36,940
I'd rather be the missing piece

201
00:11:36,940 --> 00:11:38,160
in the puzzle.

202
00:11:38,540 --> 00:11:40,130
Good for you.

203
00:11:40,150 --> 00:11:42,610
Only you care about
the finer things in life.

204
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:46,570
My finer things are right here.

205
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:48,250
I'm here to open a homestay.

206
00:11:48,330 --> 00:11:50,880
Okay. Just don't open it
next to our house.

207
00:11:53,310 --> 00:11:54,400
Arzugul,

208
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:55,640
tell me,

209
00:11:55,640 --> 00:11:57,590
if you're not comfortable living there,

210
00:11:57,590 --> 00:11:58,680
I will clear out

211
00:11:58,680 --> 00:11:59,990
the biggest room on the second floor

212
00:11:59,990 --> 00:12:00,990
for you, okay?

213
00:12:01,350 --> 00:12:03,630
Uncle, I live very well up there.

214
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:04,880
I still have things to do in the company,

215
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:06,130
so I have to go back quickly.

216
00:12:06,130 --> 00:12:07,520
I'll go back and spend time with my mom

217
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:09,050
and leave tomorrow or the day after.

218
00:12:09,050 --> 00:12:09,570
You-

219
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:10,490
Sweetie,

220
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:14,310
work can be done anytime, right?

221
00:12:14,610 --> 00:12:16,910
Arzugul, you came back from Shanghai

222
00:12:16,930 --> 00:12:19,600
and haven't even eaten my almond tart yet.

223
00:12:20,920 --> 00:12:22,300
Grandma,

224
00:12:22,330 --> 00:12:24,040
I don't want to leave either.

225
00:12:24,850 --> 00:12:28,140
But the company is pushing hard.

226
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:29,990
You finally came back once.

227
00:12:29,990 --> 00:12:31,990
Why don't you
spend more time with Grandma?

228
00:12:31,990 --> 00:12:33,990
Can the company not run without you?

229
00:12:35,470 --> 00:12:37,760
Your troupe can't run without you, right?

230
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:39,660
Your foot is swollen like that,

231
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:42,140
but you still have to dance in high heels.

232
00:12:42,590 --> 00:12:43,490
Arzugul,

233
00:12:43,980 --> 00:12:45,730
You finally came back to Kashgar

234
00:12:45,730 --> 00:12:47,850
from Shanghai.

235
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:51,300
Don't you buy some gifts
for your colleagues?

236
00:12:51,570 --> 00:12:52,560
Minawar,

237
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:53,990
today is the grand bazaar.

238
00:12:53,990 --> 00:12:55,380
You take Arzugul

239
00:12:55,760 --> 00:12:56,950
there for a walk.

240
00:12:56,950 --> 00:12:57,670
I...

241
00:12:57,990 --> 00:12:59,850
have to go back to the troupe later.

242
00:12:59,850 --> 00:13:01,230
It's fine, I know the way.

243
00:13:01,230 --> 00:13:02,180
I can go by myself.

244
00:13:02,180 --> 00:13:03,210
Minawar,

245
00:13:03,380 --> 00:13:04,310
didn't you say

246
00:13:04,310 --> 00:13:07,260
you were going to the bazaar
to buy things this afternoon?

247
00:13:07,260 --> 00:13:08,490
Why haven't you left yet?

248
00:13:08,490 --> 00:13:09,070
No.

249
00:13:09,260 --> 00:13:10,950
Look at the time.

250
00:13:10,970 --> 00:13:12,210
They're closing soon.

251
00:13:12,210 --> 00:13:13,040
Go now.

252
00:13:13,210 --> 00:13:14,270
It's running late.

253
00:13:14,490 --> 00:13:15,830
I've told you since you were little

254
00:13:15,830 --> 00:13:17,490
that you should dress up nicely
when visiting the bazaar.

255
00:13:17,490 --> 00:13:18,650
Look at you now.

256
00:13:20,850 --> 00:13:21,400
Here.

257
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:26,840
Uncle.

258
00:13:26,860 --> 00:13:27,990
Let me do it.

259
00:13:29,990 --> 00:13:30,800
Alright.

260
00:13:31,070 --> 00:13:31,880
Here you go.

261
00:14:42,220 --> 00:14:44,480
I'm on a diet. I don't drink sweet things.

262
00:14:49,090 --> 00:14:51,090
Are you really here to buy things?

263
00:14:51,960 --> 00:14:53,610
Have you been away for too long
and forgotten it?

264
00:14:53,610 --> 00:14:55,420
When us women visit the bazaar,

265
00:14:55,420 --> 00:14:56,540
it's mainly to show off

266
00:14:56,540 --> 00:14:58,020
our beauty and clothes.

267
00:14:58,020 --> 00:14:59,900
Buying things is just an excuse.

268
00:15:02,580 --> 00:15:03,840
Did you bring perfume?

269
00:15:10,970 --> 00:15:12,090
What's this smell?

270
00:15:12,110 --> 00:15:13,030
Woody scent.

271
00:15:13,810 --> 00:15:15,900
You might as well plant a tree at home
instead of wearing this.

272
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:16,690
When you wear perfume,

273
00:15:16,690 --> 00:15:18,180
it should be floral.

274
00:15:18,180 --> 00:15:19,900
Like walking into a garden.

275
00:15:23,610 --> 00:15:26,060
I heard your house is built.

276
00:15:26,060 --> 00:15:27,590
Over 20,000 a square meter.

277
00:15:27,850 --> 00:15:28,650
So expensive.

278
00:15:29,180 --> 00:15:31,940
I'll take you to see
our new house someday.

279
00:15:31,940 --> 00:15:33,780
The best neighborhood in Kashgar.

280
00:15:33,780 --> 00:15:35,450
We bought 300 to 400 square meters.

281
00:15:35,450 --> 00:15:36,420
How big is yours?

282
00:15:36,890 --> 00:15:38,150
Over 60 square meters.

283
00:15:39,260 --> 00:15:40,450
That's so small.

284
00:15:40,450 --> 00:15:43,250
I really don't know
what you're after in Shanghai.

285
00:15:43,730 --> 00:15:45,300
We don't have

286
00:15:45,690 --> 00:15:47,300
to force a conversation.

287
00:15:47,540 --> 00:15:48,810
How about we go our separate ways?

288
00:15:48,810 --> 00:15:49,520
Sure.

289
00:16:01,810 --> 00:16:03,780
Where can I buy a Yengisar knife?

290
00:16:04,330 --> 00:16:06,020
Let's go, I'll show you around.

291
00:16:06,020 --> 00:16:07,040
Come take a look.

292
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:08,810
Handmade Yengisar knives.

293
00:16:08,810 --> 00:16:10,540
Come take a look, beauties.

294
00:16:10,540 --> 00:16:11,540
Handmade knives.

295
00:16:12,060 --> 00:16:13,070
Let me see this one.

296
00:16:13,070 --> 00:16:13,940
Okay, beauty.

297
00:16:19,810 --> 00:16:20,660
How much is this one?

298
00:16:20,660 --> 00:16:21,090
800.

299
00:16:22,310 --> 00:16:23,420
You're Minawar's friend,

300
00:16:23,420 --> 00:16:24,540
I'll give you a discount.

301
00:16:24,540 --> 00:16:25,300
660.

302
00:16:25,810 --> 00:16:26,540
Alright.

303
00:16:26,540 --> 00:16:27,540
Since Minawar said so,

304
00:16:27,540 --> 00:16:28,260
it's a deal.

305
00:16:28,260 --> 00:16:28,940
Wait a minute.

306
00:16:28,940 --> 00:16:29,780
I just threw out a number.

307
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:30,690
I'm not the one buying.

308
00:16:30,690 --> 00:16:31,180
It's fine.

309
00:16:31,180 --> 00:16:32,540
660 it is.

310
00:16:32,540 --> 00:16:33,540
For good luck.

311
00:16:33,670 --> 00:16:34,670
Are you crazy?

312
00:16:34,690 --> 00:16:36,290
Spending 600 on a knife.

313
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,400
Does money grow on trees for you?

314
00:16:38,750 --> 00:16:40,040
I'm giving it to a client.

315
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:41,840
Of course I have to buy a nice one.

316
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:45,640
When did you become so tactful?

317
00:16:46,350 --> 00:16:48,610
Just doing what it takes to make a living.

318
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:53,660
Come take a look.

319
00:16:53,660 --> 00:16:55,560
A batch of amazing
tumbler pigeons arrived today.

320
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:56,850
They're so incredible that once they fly,

321
00:16:56,850 --> 00:16:58,440
they can do 6 or 7 somersaults in a row.

322
00:16:58,440 --> 00:16:59,640
Come take a look.

323
00:16:59,640 --> 00:17:01,520
A batch of amazing
tumbler pigeons arrived today.

324
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:02,880
They're so incredible that once they fly,

325
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:04,040
they can do 6 or 7 somersaults in a row.

326
00:17:04,040 --> 00:17:04,920
Then they dive straight down,

327
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:06,760
and when they're
just 6 cm from the ground,

328
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:07,750
they can suddenly fly back up.

329
00:17:07,750 --> 00:17:09,510
If you don't like it,
you don't have to pay.

330
00:17:09,510 --> 00:17:11,790
What I brought today
are all top-notch goods.

331
00:17:11,790 --> 00:17:12,440
Thank you.

332
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:14,680
Put my hat down.

333
00:17:15,710 --> 00:17:16,400
Friend,

334
00:17:16,440 --> 00:17:17,440
are you buying pigeons?

335
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:18,530
Come here, look.

336
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:20,030
These pigeons of mine,

337
00:17:20,030 --> 00:17:21,640
when they fly into the sky,

338
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:23,400
they can do 7 or 8 somersaults.

339
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:24,680
And when they almost hit the ground,

340
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:25,750
they fly back up.

341
00:17:25,839 --> 00:17:27,030
They also know the way.

342
00:17:27,030 --> 00:17:27,790
They know the way.

343
00:17:27,790 --> 00:17:29,230
No matter how far they fly,

344
00:17:29,230 --> 00:17:30,630
if you blow this whistle,

345
00:17:32,360 --> 00:17:34,320
they'll fly right back.

346
00:17:35,270 --> 00:17:37,440
Re-really?

347
00:17:37,440 --> 00:17:38,680
Of course it's true, friend.

348
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:39,250
Friend,

349
00:17:39,470 --> 00:17:40,920
since your pigeons are so amazing,

350
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:42,080
can they help me find someone

351
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:43,320
in this bazaar?

352
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:44,920
Friend,

353
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:46,550
you can just buy it.

354
00:17:46,550 --> 00:17:47,840
These are not eagles.

355
00:17:47,840 --> 00:17:49,700
How can they find someone for you?

356
00:17:50,710 --> 00:17:52,180
Come take a look.

357
00:18:14,050 --> 00:18:15,210
Help!

358
00:18:21,770 --> 00:18:22,690
Help!

359
00:18:24,810 --> 00:18:26,050
Help!

360
00:18:30,840 --> 00:18:32,700
Xia Zi!

361
00:18:32,730 --> 00:18:33,770
Are you okay, Xia Zi?

362
00:18:33,770 --> 00:18:34,290
I'm fine.

363
00:18:34,290 --> 00:18:35,550
Are you hurt anywhere?

364
00:18:36,140 --> 00:18:36,820
What's wrong with you?

365
00:18:36,820 --> 00:18:38,340
If you don't watch your sheep,

366
00:18:38,340 --> 00:18:39,800
what if they hurt someone?

367
00:18:40,250 --> 00:18:41,050
Xia Zi.

368
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:43,420
Fang Nan.

369
00:18:44,730 --> 00:18:45,530
Are you okay?

370
00:18:45,530 --> 00:18:46,080
I'm fine.

371
00:18:46,080 --> 00:18:47,380
Why is it you?

372
00:18:49,150 --> 00:18:50,320
I'm sorry.

373
00:18:52,410 --> 00:18:53,140
It's okay.

374
00:18:53,690 --> 00:18:54,340
It's okay.

375
00:18:58,690 --> 00:19:00,160
Have you ever imagined

376
00:19:00,160 --> 00:19:00,690
Have some.

377
00:19:00,690 --> 00:19:01,010
Sure.

378
00:19:01,010 --> 00:19:04,470
the scene of reuniting
with your first love after years apart?

379
00:19:04,660 --> 00:19:06,660
I've rehearsed it countless times.

380
00:19:07,340 --> 00:19:09,470
A chance encounter at a street corner,

381
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:12,530
a class reunion
where everyone has their own agenda,

382
00:19:12,660 --> 00:19:14,180
or someone's wedding,

383
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:15,790
or even

384
00:19:16,310 --> 00:19:17,760
someone's funeral.

385
00:19:18,750 --> 00:19:21,380
When I saw Fang Nan again at the bazaar,

386
00:19:22,350 --> 00:19:25,500
I thought this was the most reasonable.

387
00:19:27,510 --> 00:19:29,040
The bazaar is like a father,

388
00:19:29,450 --> 00:19:30,510
and also a mother.

389
00:19:31,580 --> 00:19:33,710
The bazaar is everything in the world.

390
00:19:34,970 --> 00:19:37,940
So, of course, anything
can happen in the bazaar.

391
00:19:43,210 --> 00:19:44,750
Oh, stop wiping.

392
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:45,680
You can't wipe it off.

393
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:47,050
You have to wash it.

394
00:19:47,680 --> 00:19:48,440
That...

395
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:49,940
should be cow dung.

396
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:52,180
It can be rubbed off with water.

397
00:19:52,180 --> 00:19:54,550
Do you want to go
wash it off in my sheepfold?

398
00:19:54,550 --> 00:19:55,750
You have a sheepfold?

399
00:19:56,030 --> 00:19:57,290
What are you doing now?

400
00:19:57,600 --> 00:19:58,790
I sell sheep.

401
00:19:58,990 --> 00:19:59,750
My sheepfold

402
00:19:59,750 --> 00:20:01,510
is right on the way back to the city.

403
00:20:01,510 --> 00:20:04,160
I remember you went to Urumqi for college.

404
00:20:04,510 --> 00:20:05,970
Why are you selling sheep?

405
00:20:07,450 --> 00:20:08,450
Don't bring it up.

406
00:20:09,330 --> 00:20:11,230
I feel big cities don't suit me at all.

407
00:20:11,230 --> 00:20:12,490
Our Kashgar is better.

408
00:20:12,640 --> 00:20:13,320
How about you?

409
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:14,030
I heard

410
00:20:14,030 --> 00:20:16,120
you're doing pretty well in Shanghai.

411
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:17,190
Not really.

412
00:20:17,190 --> 00:20:18,440
Just average.

413
00:20:18,470 --> 00:20:19,630
Our Arzugul

414
00:20:19,660 --> 00:20:20,830
is now an executive at a

415
00:20:20,830 --> 00:20:22,030
real estate company in Shanghai.

416
00:20:22,030 --> 00:20:23,690
Don't listen to her nonsense.

417
00:20:24,290 --> 00:20:25,900
You don't need to be modest.

418
00:20:25,930 --> 00:20:27,560
You were always number one growing up.

419
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:30,220
I'm not surprised at all
that you're doing well.

420
00:20:32,660 --> 00:20:33,660
How is Ms. Li?

421
00:20:33,860 --> 00:20:34,790
She's fine.

422
00:20:34,790 --> 00:20:36,160
My mom is retired now.

423
00:20:36,220 --> 00:20:38,880
She travels around every day
and is rarely seen.

424
00:20:43,250 --> 00:20:44,490
Are...

425
00:20:46,420 --> 00:20:47,580
Are you married?

426
00:20:49,270 --> 00:20:50,320
Who would I marry?

427
00:20:50,320 --> 00:20:52,720
It's good enough
that I can support myself.

428
00:20:54,510 --> 00:20:56,710
How long has it been
since we last saw each other?

429
00:20:56,710 --> 00:20:57,490
7 years?

430
00:20:58,380 --> 00:20:59,190
No.

431
00:20:59,580 --> 00:21:02,580
It's been 7 years
since we graduated from high school.

432
00:21:02,660 --> 00:21:03,660
But for us,

433
00:21:04,100 --> 00:21:06,010
it will be 6 years in 2 months.

434
00:21:08,050 --> 00:21:09,180
The last time we saw each other

435
00:21:09,180 --> 00:21:10,860
was during the summer vacation
of our freshman year,

436
00:21:10,860 --> 00:21:12,540
at the class reunion.

437
00:21:13,950 --> 00:21:15,480
I remember you didn't come.

438
00:21:19,010 --> 00:21:19,730
Right.

439
00:21:21,430 --> 00:21:22,490
Let me add you on WeChat.

440
00:21:22,490 --> 00:21:24,010
I only have your QQ,

441
00:21:24,010 --> 00:21:25,010
and you're never online.

442
00:21:25,010 --> 00:21:27,490
Are you two putting on
a blind date show in front of me?

443
00:21:27,490 --> 00:21:28,450
Should I leave?

444
00:21:28,580 --> 00:21:29,140
No.

445
00:21:29,140 --> 00:21:30,210
We've been classmates for so many years.

446
00:21:30,210 --> 00:21:31,380
Just adding WeChat.

447
00:21:31,660 --> 00:21:32,490
Help!

448
00:21:32,660 --> 00:21:34,690
The lamb was born not breathing.

449
00:21:34,690 --> 00:21:35,900
Come, help!

450
00:21:36,250 --> 00:21:37,530
Can someone help?

451
00:21:37,950 --> 00:21:40,750
Can someone help?
The lamb was born not breathing.

452
00:21:42,970 --> 00:21:44,120
Here, give it to me.

453
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:45,400
Let me see.

454
00:22:02,140 --> 00:22:05,050
Thank you.

455
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:06,210
Thank you, Mr. Fang.

456
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:08,440
Mr. Fang, thanks to you.

457
00:22:08,620 --> 00:22:10,050
The new-breed lambs you sent over

458
00:22:10,050 --> 00:22:11,250
from your breeding base last time

459
00:22:11,250 --> 00:22:12,970
are really good.

460
00:22:12,970 --> 00:22:14,140
You're welcome.

461
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:14,760
Thank you.

462
00:22:15,010 --> 00:22:15,730
Mr. Fang?

463
00:22:15,990 --> 00:22:17,340
Aren't you a sheep seller?

464
00:22:17,340 --> 00:22:18,490
A sheep seller?

465
00:22:18,550 --> 00:22:19,480
No, no, no.

466
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:23,180
Mr. Fang is the youngest
engineer in our station.

467
00:22:23,180 --> 00:22:24,750
He does scientific research,

468
00:22:24,750 --> 00:22:25,990
and works on big projects.

469
00:22:25,990 --> 00:22:27,190
He's amazing.

470
00:22:27,190 --> 00:22:28,130
No.

471
00:22:28,270 --> 00:22:29,840
I do sell sheep,

472
00:22:29,840 --> 00:22:31,470
but our breeding base

473
00:22:31,470 --> 00:22:32,510
isn't for money.

474
00:22:32,510 --> 00:22:34,440
It's for data collection samples.

475
00:22:35,540 --> 00:22:36,690
Can I hold it?

476
00:22:36,770 --> 00:22:37,680
Sure.

477
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:39,030
Careful.

478
00:22:39,510 --> 00:22:40,550
Be careful.

479
00:22:40,550 --> 00:22:41,440
Like this.

480
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,440
Support its bottom with your hands.

481
00:22:43,620 --> 00:22:44,140
Right.

482
00:22:45,380 --> 00:22:46,430
I'm not very good at this.

483
00:22:46,430 --> 00:22:47,890
It's okay. This works too.

484
00:22:50,770 --> 00:22:53,940
Look at its nose bridge.
It's as high as Minawar's.

485
00:22:56,230 --> 00:22:57,630
Its mother is calling it.

486
00:22:58,680 --> 00:22:59,810
We're leaving, sir.

487
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:01,880
-Thank you.
-Bye.

488
00:23:03,380 --> 00:23:05,510
It wasn't easy. He saved it.

489
00:23:08,140 --> 00:23:09,440
We haven't seen each other for so long.

490
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:10,190
It's rare to run into you,

491
00:23:10,190 --> 00:23:11,680
and I couldn't even treat you to a meal.

492
00:23:11,680 --> 00:23:13,480
It's fine. We ate before coming.

493
00:23:15,720 --> 00:23:16,880
Sir, let's go.

494
00:23:19,790 --> 00:23:20,360
How...

495
00:23:20,360 --> 00:23:22,270
How long are you staying this time?

496
00:23:22,270 --> 00:23:23,930
I'll leave in a couple of days.

497
00:23:25,710 --> 00:23:26,320
Well...

498
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:28,230
Alright.

499
00:23:28,230 --> 00:23:29,030
I'm leaving.

500
00:23:29,270 --> 00:23:29,950
Bye.

501
00:23:42,070 --> 00:23:51,900
[Six years ago]

502
00:24:14,470 --> 00:24:15,340
Fang Nan.

503
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:17,950
Is this almond necklace

504
00:24:18,340 --> 00:24:19,450
for me?

505
00:24:21,190 --> 00:24:22,300
It's for Xia Zi.

506
00:24:25,660 --> 00:24:27,920
She's going to college in Shanghai.

507
00:24:28,770 --> 00:24:30,510
She has seen so much of the world.

508
00:24:30,510 --> 00:24:31,910
Would she even like this?

509
00:24:46,900 --> 00:24:48,660
Did I remember it wrong?

510
00:24:49,250 --> 00:24:52,140
Fang Nan said the last time we met was

511
00:24:52,140 --> 00:24:54,100
at the class reunion that summer.

512
00:24:54,620 --> 00:24:56,380
But I remember he didn't come.

513
00:25:09,340 --> 00:25:10,620
Happy wedding.

514
00:25:10,620 --> 00:25:11,510
A gift for you.

515
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:17,050
As soon as I saw this box,

516
00:25:17,210 --> 00:25:19,010
I felt like it had your name on it.

517
00:25:23,270 --> 00:25:24,210
Thank you.

518
00:25:24,530 --> 00:25:25,730
I wish you happiness.

519
00:25:30,380 --> 00:25:31,750
Did you use to like him?

520
00:25:32,360 --> 00:25:34,210
You were the one who liked him.

521
00:25:34,210 --> 00:25:36,540
There was absolutely nothing between us.

522
00:25:37,360 --> 00:25:39,160
My fiance is so rich.

523
00:25:39,440 --> 00:25:41,190
Who cares about Fang Nan?

524
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:46,840
Come, let's take a picture together.

525
00:25:46,840 --> 00:25:48,080
Let's take it later.

526
00:25:50,550 --> 00:25:52,320
Cheese.

527
00:25:55,010 --> 00:25:56,920
Great.

528
00:26:00,890 --> 00:26:02,410
Minawar!

529
00:26:05,990 --> 00:26:08,030
You're going to Shanghai now.

530
00:26:08,030 --> 00:26:09,160
Are you ignoring us?

531
00:26:09,530 --> 00:26:10,120
I am not.

532
00:26:10,120 --> 00:26:12,050
I texted you, but you didn't reply.

533
00:26:12,150 --> 00:26:13,780
Tell me how you've been.

534
00:26:16,080 --> 00:26:16,830
I...

535
00:26:17,270 --> 00:26:19,870
am joining the regional
song and dance troupe.

536
00:26:23,690 --> 00:26:26,140
Weren't you going to
apply for the dance academy

537
00:26:26,140 --> 00:26:28,000
and coming to Shanghai to find me?

538
00:26:30,750 --> 00:26:32,600
Not everyone is as lucky as you are,

539
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:33,680
Xia Zi.

540
00:26:37,920 --> 00:26:39,330
Hey, you're here.

541
00:26:47,500 --> 00:26:49,040
A book says that

542
00:26:49,660 --> 00:26:50,680
in this world,

543
00:26:51,130 --> 00:26:53,060
there are only two types of people.

544
00:26:53,390 --> 00:26:54,540
Those who leave,

545
00:26:55,270 --> 00:26:56,440
and those who stay.

546
00:26:58,270 --> 00:26:59,160
Back then,

547
00:26:59,710 --> 00:27:00,820
I left.

548
00:27:02,250 --> 00:27:03,690
My hometown and friends

549
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:05,690
were all left behind.

550
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:08,030
Now,

551
00:27:09,250 --> 00:27:10,580
I am a bit envious of

552
00:27:10,970 --> 00:27:12,580
the friends who stayed.

553
00:27:36,480 --> 00:27:37,480
Mom.

554
00:27:41,140 --> 00:27:42,080
Adili.

555
00:27:44,230 --> 00:27:46,160
I encountered a mudslide on the mountain.

556
00:27:46,160 --> 00:27:47,490
Sorry to make you worry.

557
00:27:47,530 --> 00:27:48,160
Mom.

558
00:27:50,660 --> 00:27:51,250
Mom.

559
00:27:52,450 --> 00:27:54,380
Count them. See if any are missing.

560
00:28:16,270 --> 00:28:16,950
Adili,

561
00:28:17,950 --> 00:28:19,010
what are you doing?

562
00:28:19,640 --> 00:28:20,900
What are you thinking?

563
00:28:21,210 --> 00:28:22,640
She's getting married.

564
00:28:23,290 --> 00:28:26,020
Why are you more persistent
than the wind in the Gobi?

565
00:28:26,020 --> 00:28:27,720
No matter how deep your feelings are,

566
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:30,450
you can't move someone
who has made up their mind.

567
00:28:30,470 --> 00:28:31,590
None of your business.

568
00:28:31,590 --> 00:28:32,240
Go home.

569
00:28:50,080 --> 00:28:53,010
This is the handmade chocolate
you asked me to bring.

570
00:28:53,350 --> 00:28:54,110
Thank you.

571
00:28:54,550 --> 00:28:56,180
How much is it? I'll transfer it to you.

572
00:28:56,180 --> 00:28:57,580
No need. It's very cheap.

573
00:28:58,190 --> 00:28:59,680
I can't just take it.

574
00:28:59,940 --> 00:29:01,920
You always bring things for me.

575
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:03,900
It's no trouble at all.

576
00:29:09,600 --> 00:29:10,530
How have you been

577
00:29:10,610 --> 00:29:11,850
lately?

578
00:29:14,510 --> 00:29:15,490
I've been good.

579
00:29:15,970 --> 00:29:16,640
Do you know

580
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:18,190
who I ran into the other day?

581
00:29:20,100 --> 00:29:20,820
Fang Nan.

582
00:29:21,190 --> 00:29:22,160
Fang Nan?

583
00:29:22,730 --> 00:29:24,830
I ran into him with Arzugul.

584
00:29:26,120 --> 00:29:27,710
When I saw him that day,

585
00:29:28,010 --> 00:29:30,270
I felt like we were back in our childhood.

586
00:29:31,030 --> 00:29:32,550
I remember

587
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:34,680
you and Arzugul had a falling out

588
00:29:35,400 --> 00:29:37,460
because of Fang Nan back then, right?

589
00:29:38,840 --> 00:29:41,190
Stop thinking that girls only fight

590
00:29:41,190 --> 00:29:42,640
over men, okay?

591
00:29:42,730 --> 00:29:44,290
Men aren't that important.

592
00:29:45,210 --> 00:29:46,190
But I see that you two have been

593
00:29:46,190 --> 00:29:47,880
at odds all these years.

594
00:29:48,620 --> 00:29:50,750
Back then, Fang Nan always

595
00:29:50,750 --> 00:29:52,680
hung out with us to pursue Arzugul.

596
00:29:52,820 --> 00:29:54,640
I thought he liked me.

597
00:29:55,270 --> 00:29:56,270
It's that simple.

598
00:29:56,560 --> 00:29:57,560
That simple?

599
00:30:00,440 --> 00:30:01,460
Later,

600
00:30:02,280 --> 00:30:04,190
Arzugul went to college

601
00:30:04,670 --> 00:30:05,910
in Shanghai,

602
00:30:06,710 --> 00:30:08,300
stayed there,

603
00:30:09,570 --> 00:30:11,650
and then bought a house there.

604
00:30:12,670 --> 00:30:13,650
And I

605
00:30:15,320 --> 00:30:16,870
have always been here,

606
00:30:17,620 --> 00:30:18,990
unable to go anywhere.

607
00:30:21,550 --> 00:30:23,350
I'm inferior to her in every way.

608
00:30:27,230 --> 00:30:29,300
You've never been inferior to Arzugul.

609
00:30:29,300 --> 00:30:30,690
I've always said so,

610
00:30:30,790 --> 00:30:32,520
but you just never believed it.

611
00:30:39,240 --> 00:30:40,600
Let me try this candy.

612
00:30:40,950 --> 00:30:42,030
If it's good,

613
00:30:42,990 --> 00:30:45,270
I'll buy a lot for the gifts

614
00:30:45,830 --> 00:30:46,860
at my wedding.

615
00:30:49,470 --> 00:30:50,580
You must

616
00:30:50,580 --> 00:30:51,980
come early to my wedding.

617
00:31:21,470 --> 00:31:23,690
New city,

618
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:26,470
new beginning.

619
00:31:33,600 --> 00:31:34,640
Sir,

620
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:36,600
can I help you?

621
00:31:36,880 --> 00:31:38,080
Who are you?

622
00:31:38,580 --> 00:31:39,770
Where's Wang?

623
00:31:41,880 --> 00:31:42,950
This is my shop.

624
00:31:43,470 --> 00:31:44,550
-He rented it to me.
-Your shop?

625
00:31:44,550 --> 00:31:46,370
Yes, and now I run this guesthouse.

626
00:31:46,370 --> 00:31:47,330
To you?

627
00:31:47,360 --> 00:31:48,990
I am the landlord.

628
00:31:49,010 --> 00:31:50,000
Leave.

629
00:31:50,030 --> 00:31:51,090
No, sir.

630
00:31:51,110 --> 00:31:52,310
You must be mistaken.

631
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:55,410
He said he rented this
from you for 5 years.

632
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:56,600
We just signed the contract.

633
00:31:56,600 --> 00:31:57,360
Contract?

634
00:31:57,790 --> 00:31:59,190
I won't look at it.
The lease has expired, no more renting.

635
00:31:59,190 --> 00:32:00,680
Sir, I've already paid.

636
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:01,950
I gave him 100,000 a year.

637
00:32:01,950 --> 00:32:02,340
What?

638
00:32:02,340 --> 00:32:03,160
You can take a look.

639
00:32:03,160 --> 00:32:04,190
100,000?

640
00:32:04,550 --> 00:32:06,360
He only gave me 30,000!

641
00:32:06,360 --> 00:32:07,270
Leave.

642
00:32:07,270 --> 00:32:08,120
Go away.

643
00:32:08,120 --> 00:32:09,470
-Sir, I've paid the rent.
-Leave.

644
00:32:09,470 --> 00:32:10,030
Leave.

645
00:32:10,030 --> 00:32:11,560
I have the transfer record.

646
00:32:12,190 --> 00:32:13,360
Sir, is there a misunderstanding?

647
00:32:13,360 --> 00:32:13,710
Sir!

648
00:32:13,710 --> 00:32:14,440
Leave.

649
00:32:16,460 --> 00:32:17,160
Wait, sir.

650
00:32:18,060 --> 00:32:18,610
Leave

651
00:32:18,630 --> 00:32:19,220
Go away.

652
00:32:36,270 --> 00:32:37,920
Mom.

653
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:40,250
Mom!

654
00:32:41,660 --> 00:32:42,270
Wake up.

655
00:32:45,100 --> 00:32:45,900
You scared me.

656
00:32:45,920 --> 00:32:47,640
How are you so strong?

657
00:32:48,890 --> 00:32:50,530
You pressed so hard. My chest hurts.

658
00:32:50,530 --> 00:32:51,380
What are you doing?

659
00:32:51,380 --> 00:32:52,190
You scared me.

660
00:32:52,190 --> 00:32:54,140
Right. Don't speak yet.

661
00:32:55,110 --> 00:32:56,400
I'm afraid I'd forget.

662
00:32:56,420 --> 00:32:57,940
Let me write it down.

663
00:33:00,710 --> 00:33:03,210
It has an analgesic effect.

664
00:33:04,100 --> 00:33:05,720
If you take too much, it will have

665
00:33:05,720 --> 00:33:08,130
a sedative and sleep-inducing effect.

666
00:33:11,050 --> 00:33:13,510
Are you playing
Shennong tasting the herbs?

667
00:33:14,610 --> 00:33:15,720
What else?

668
00:33:15,750 --> 00:33:16,790
Once your father died,

669
00:33:16,790 --> 00:33:18,650
your mother has to seek death too?

670
00:33:19,380 --> 00:33:20,180
Don't worry.

671
00:33:20,770 --> 00:33:22,530
I'm not that fragile.

672
00:33:25,440 --> 00:33:26,450
Why are you back?

673
00:33:27,850 --> 00:33:28,330
I...

674
00:33:29,960 --> 00:33:31,760
I'm going back to Shanghai soon.

675
00:33:32,380 --> 00:33:34,110
I came back to keep you company.

676
00:33:42,850 --> 00:33:45,050
Why are there so many flowers suddenly?

677
00:33:47,190 --> 00:33:48,210
Look.

678
00:33:48,620 --> 00:33:50,290
These Panax notoginseng,

679
00:33:50,520 --> 00:33:52,760
mint, honeysuckle,

680
00:33:53,530 --> 00:33:54,790
each one is a treasure.

681
00:33:57,530 --> 00:33:59,380
Birth, aging, sickness and death

682
00:33:59,380 --> 00:34:01,420
are like the rotation of the four seasons,

683
00:34:01,420 --> 00:34:02,580
all natural laws.

684
00:34:04,190 --> 00:34:06,450
We should let go of your father's matter.

685
00:34:14,320 --> 00:34:15,040
Mom.

686
00:34:16,690 --> 00:34:18,570
Regarding my father's death,

687
00:34:19,489 --> 00:34:21,949
I really can't accept
his sudden departure.

688
00:34:22,090 --> 00:34:23,500
I am not as detached as you,

689
00:34:23,500 --> 00:34:24,630
nor as open-minded.

690
00:34:25,469 --> 00:34:27,070
I can't let go so quickly.

691
00:34:27,739 --> 00:34:29,540
Seeing you tough it out like this

692
00:34:29,860 --> 00:34:31,260
makes me feel even worse.

693
00:34:50,320 --> 00:34:51,340
Your father,

694
00:34:52,630 --> 00:34:54,350
a man of over 80 kg,

695
00:34:55,310 --> 00:34:57,310
was brought back in such a light box.

696
00:35:00,360 --> 00:35:02,380
Do you think my heart doesn't hurt?

697
00:35:17,340 --> 00:35:18,040
Take this.

698
00:35:25,730 --> 00:35:27,960
I still have to
revise prescriptions tonight.

699
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:29,800
You don't have to come all the way here.

700
00:35:29,800 --> 00:35:30,640
Go back.

701
00:35:32,920 --> 00:35:35,720
I've been used to being alone
for so many years.

702
00:35:35,860 --> 00:35:38,260
Just go back to Shanghai
with peace of mind.

703
00:35:38,450 --> 00:35:40,490
Life still has to go on.

704
00:35:44,490 --> 00:35:47,430
I still have a bunch of
little babies to take care of.

705
00:36:17,390 --> 00:36:18,470
Hello, Mr. Li.

706
00:36:18,500 --> 00:36:19,940
You're still up so late.

707
00:36:20,650 --> 00:36:22,780
Have you sorted out the things at home?

708
00:36:24,220 --> 00:36:25,150
Yes, I have.

709
00:36:25,970 --> 00:36:26,840
Rest assured.

710
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:29,810
I'll definitely hurry up to make up for

711
00:36:29,920 --> 00:36:32,170
the unfinished work
from before these days.

712
00:36:32,170 --> 00:36:32,950
I have a client

713
00:36:32,950 --> 00:36:35,370
who really likes
the Yengisar knives from here.

714
00:36:35,370 --> 00:36:37,030
I bought one for him this time.

715
00:36:38,550 --> 00:36:39,630
There is something

716
00:36:39,630 --> 00:36:41,150
I need to inform you about.

717
00:36:43,260 --> 00:36:44,090
Go ahead.

718
00:36:44,400 --> 00:36:47,110
Recently, the company
has made structural adjustments,

719
00:36:47,110 --> 00:36:50,220
decided to reduce costs, increase
efficiency, and cut sales positions.

720
00:36:50,220 --> 00:36:52,420
It's not that I haven't warned you before.

721
00:36:52,420 --> 00:36:53,070
Your team

722
00:36:53,070 --> 00:36:54,670
has been at the bottom
in performance more than once.

723
00:36:54,670 --> 00:36:56,990
I've told you so many times,
but there's no improvement.

724
00:36:56,990 --> 00:36:58,520
Everyone competes fairly.

725
00:36:58,550 --> 00:37:00,800
Eliminating the worst performers
is company policy.

726
00:37:00,800 --> 00:37:04,060
Come back as soon as possible
and handle your resignation.

727
00:37:08,380 --> 00:37:10,180
Hello, the number you dialed...

728
00:37:10,200 --> 00:37:11,800
Wang, answer the phone.

729
00:37:15,960 --> 00:37:18,080
It's Zhou Hengzhi!

730
00:37:21,300 --> 00:37:22,260
You know me?

731
00:37:23,450 --> 00:37:24,700
Poor guy.

732
00:37:24,700 --> 00:37:27,560
You rented an empty house
from the old miser Mehmet,

733
00:37:27,570 --> 00:37:29,050
and were scammed out of 100,000 yuan

734
00:37:29,050 --> 00:37:30,470
by your best friend.

735
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:33,970
H-how did you know?

736
00:37:33,970 --> 00:37:34,940
Of course we know.

737
00:37:34,940 --> 00:37:36,800
Our friend Abudu told us.

738
00:37:53,420 --> 00:37:54,760
Oh, please.

739
00:38:08,220 --> 00:38:09,940
Don't be angry.

740
00:38:09,940 --> 00:38:11,650
Anger feeds the devil.

741
00:38:11,650 --> 00:38:13,280
Don't worry.

742
00:38:13,280 --> 00:38:14,740
Worry makes you die early.

743
00:38:14,970 --> 00:38:16,570
Don't be anxious.

744
00:38:36,720 --> 00:38:37,450
Hi.

745
00:38:39,030 --> 00:38:40,160
What a coincidence.

746
00:38:40,410 --> 00:38:41,510
Are you here...

747
00:38:42,570 --> 00:38:43,420
for a walk?

748
00:38:44,900 --> 00:38:46,160
Want to walk together?

749
00:38:46,770 --> 00:38:47,660
I'm hungry.

750
00:38:53,820 --> 00:38:55,130
So,

751
00:38:55,780 --> 00:38:57,340
you paid all the money,

752
00:38:58,010 --> 00:38:59,650
and your friend ran away?

753
00:39:02,520 --> 00:39:03,770
Who said

754
00:39:04,070 --> 00:39:06,670
he wanted to be
the missing piece of the puzzle?

755
00:39:07,800 --> 00:39:09,630
I admit, I was slapped in the face.

756
00:39:09,630 --> 00:39:10,360
Okay?

757
00:39:12,440 --> 00:39:13,840
You're talking about me?

758
00:39:14,050 --> 00:39:15,850
You're not any better yourself.

759
00:39:15,880 --> 00:39:16,880
You lost your job.

760
00:39:17,630 --> 00:39:18,690
Are you going back?

761
00:39:18,700 --> 00:39:20,130
Of course I have to.

762
00:39:20,680 --> 00:39:22,290
If I don't go back, who will pay me?

763
00:39:22,290 --> 00:39:23,710
Who will pay my mortgage?

764
00:39:24,470 --> 00:39:25,260
I think

765
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:27,340
we can celebrate.

766
00:39:28,200 --> 00:39:29,820
What to celebrate? Things are like this.

767
00:39:29,820 --> 00:39:30,470
No.

768
00:39:30,840 --> 00:39:31,840
Since things are this bad,

769
00:39:31,840 --> 00:39:33,640
they can't get any worse, right?

770
00:39:34,310 --> 00:39:36,910
What's that inspirational quote again?

771
00:39:38,840 --> 00:39:40,970
Once you pick up
all the stones at the bottom,

772
00:39:40,970 --> 00:39:43,300
the rest of your life
is an upward journey.

773
00:39:44,610 --> 00:39:46,630
You're quite good at it.

774
00:39:48,450 --> 00:39:49,260
You want some?

775
00:39:50,840 --> 00:39:51,570
Chopsticks.

776
00:39:54,970 --> 00:39:56,300
What are you looking at?

777
00:39:56,470 --> 00:39:57,180
Look.

778
00:39:59,360 --> 00:40:01,360
Who said things couldn't get worse?

779
00:40:03,340 --> 00:40:05,380
Rose Garden's construction suspended.

780
00:40:05,380 --> 00:40:07,180
Resumption date to be notified.

781
00:40:10,440 --> 00:40:11,900
Is it the house you bought?

782
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:14,940
Even if things are worse,

783
00:40:14,940 --> 00:40:16,220
this noodle

784
00:40:16,570 --> 00:40:17,670
is not too bad.

785
00:40:21,670 --> 00:40:23,780
So this is how you cheer yourself up?

786
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:34,650
Three, two, one, cheese!

787
00:40:51,090 --> 00:40:58,810
♪ An empty bowl is enough ♪

788
00:41:00,620 --> 00:41:08,800
♪ I'll take it as my wine cup ♪

789
00:41:09,730 --> 00:41:13,730
♪ My only confidants now ♪

790
00:41:14,760 --> 00:41:18,600
♪ Are these four lonely walls ♪

791
00:41:19,410 --> 00:41:22,660
♪ The sound of the dutar ♪

792
00:41:23,530 --> 00:41:26,150
♪ Has already drunk my heart ♪

793
00:41:28,140 --> 00:41:36,600
♪ I play my instrument with care ♪

794
00:41:37,900 --> 00:41:46,910
♪ So the neighbors won't be aware ♪

795
00:41:47,530 --> 00:41:56,640
♪ Take the world, I give it to you ♪

796
00:41:57,410 --> 00:42:06,910
♪ Just leave me my lonely,
sorrowful tune ♪

797
00:42:07,050 --> 00:42:11,150
♪ The dutar is my lover ♪

798
00:42:11,880 --> 00:42:16,150
♪ The dutar is my wine ♪

799
00:42:16,720 --> 00:42:20,500
♪ The dutar is where my hangovers begin ♪

800
00:42:21,640 --> 00:42:24,900
♪ Let everyone stay away ♪

801
00:42:26,510 --> 00:42:30,150
♪ Leave me here alone ♪

802
00:42:31,310 --> 00:42:34,850
♪ In grief, in sorrow, in the cold ♪

803
00:42:34,970 --> 00:42:38,380
Don't be angry.

804
00:42:36,480 --> 00:42:41,150
♪ My lover is my wine ♪

805
00:42:38,780 --> 00:42:42,490
Anger feeds the devil.

806
00:42:41,170 --> 00:42:44,640
♪ My lover is where my hangovers begin ♪

807
00:42:48,510 --> 00:42:49,900
Let me ask you something.

808
00:42:49,900 --> 00:42:50,700
The other day,

809
00:42:51,800 --> 00:42:53,990
I saw you at the grand bazaar.

810
00:42:54,670 --> 00:42:55,800
Who was that boy?

811
00:42:56,320 --> 00:42:57,840
He seemed to know you very well.
